	<p>Id think running a good bard is about as hectic as you can get.  A good bard keeps 4 songs running.  A great bard keeps 4 songs running, runs CC, assists in melee and spell damage and does it all non stop.<br />
<br />
Playing a good bard can destroy your wrists though.  I have a guildmate that is an author.  She has sat at a computer and written for hours at a time for a decade.  In the last year, since she started playing a bard, she has developed a progressive carpul tunnel illness that keeps her in pain and requires wrist supports and excercises.  But shes a HELL of a bard.<br />
<br />
And dont kid yourself, an enchanter can be just as boring as a cleric if your group demands single pulls as a rule.  I have a level 40 chanter that I never play anymore because LDoN, his main source of grouping, is incredibly boring.  I play a haste and clarity bot that might toss a mezz once in 10 pulls, only to have it broken by offtanking.  Charming?  Groups are too afraid of it to allow me to do it, even though I can solo pretty well with just charming in places like DL.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=387491" target="_blank">Thorzion Spiritcaller</a><br />
<i>...you cant fight in here, this is the War Room!</i></div>
	
	
