	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>samanna</b><br /><i>Difficult as in pressing a lot of keys frequently? Probably Bard.<br />
<br />
Difficult as in trying to stay awake on raids? Probably Cleric.<br />
<br />
Difficult as in putting up with depressing posts about class balance? Probably any except Bards, Enchanters, and 10k Tanks. Yes, even clerics complain about this.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>A bard is by far the most attention-intensive class to play if you want to play them correctly.  I've played most classes except ranger and rogue.  Clerics can be exciting to play on raids, except when you're in a CH chain.  <br />
<br />
Clerics are boring when you have nothing go wrong.  Your job is to hit CH if the damage comes in slowly, SL/HL if the damage comes in faster, Div. Arb. if the tank loses 80% in one round then SR and hope you can help the tank survive off chain SL/HLs.<br />
<br />
Enchanters are not difficult to play at all if you're aware of the surroundings.  The have the same elements as shamans (debuff, slow, use a pet) except you have to pay more attention when you're charming.  Mez is like rooting for CC except resisted mezzes can get you dead and tanks who are too impatient and break mez without taunting/aggroing can get you dead also.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
