<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Ungkor</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I'm surprised that nobody mentioned Necro.  While I agree that the bard is probably the most difficult, I'd rank a good necro as second.  Its less so at 65 for a necro though.  At lower levels when screaming terror was working on mobs, necro's could provide direct CC via their mez.  Root, rez, FD, snare, group heals, awesome aggro for kiting mobs away, offtanking with their pet, FD splitting, etc..<br />
<br />
I remember when my alt necro first got his dark pact single target hot.  I was fighting in the great divide with a group, and the cleric got swamped and had to run for a bit, the MT was low life, I pact him, he fell down, boom it ticked, ihe stood back up hehe.  This went on for a while, the tanking falling over then popping back up, while I'm casting screaming terror on one mob, then poisoning another mob off the cleric, kiting that mob around, while casting root on additional adds.  <br />
<br />
Really, any utility casting class can be  intense if played well.  I group with a friend pally who is awesome.  He's constantly assisting the mob to see if it switches targets. One time, on a raid, a named mob pulled off him.  In that split second he targets me, heals me, regains aggro, all before the cleric or druid in the group could even think about healing me.  Saved my life more times than I can recall<img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
Actually, I don't think I'd define the bard as the hardest class to play, just maybe the most annoying.  The bard has such utility, that sure, there are ton's of things you can do for any given situation.  However, classes like necro's and shamans also have great utility.  The distinction is, necro/shaman/druid etc.. don't have so many specific tools to accomplish what a bard can do, so skill wise, I'd say a great necro is actually a more skillful player than a great bard.  Its providing an amazing benefit for a group, when its an actual difficult to provide that benefit, that separates the class knowledgeable player from the skillful player.  <br />
<br />
A great bard has to know his class well.  A great shaman has to know his class, AND how to improvise to make his class perform above average<img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;postid=272548">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;do=getip&postid=272548">Logged</a></div>
	
	<!-- / message -->
		
