<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Juujuu</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 1999<br />
	Location: Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Bard is the hardest to play really well, but give some of the biggest rewards if you do it well.<br />
I remember playing the shaman in Karnors castle, doing main healing and slowing and CCing for a group of 5 melees and having to handle pulls of 4 or 5 mobs at a time back in my mid 50s.  I remember being main healer and slower for all sorts of Sebilis groups too, crawling down to disco and back or whatever camp.  Those were fun times.<br />
I haven't had the fun of doing stuff like that until I started playing my bard again.<br />
Bards are very powerful, good for almost any group, and have access to some of most useful types of spells (songs) of all classes.<br />
When I'm in a group, like ldon, I'm playing puller, charming a mob for more dps, singing haste/proccing haste off epic, singing overhaste, singing mana regen, and directing the group where to move in the dungeon.<br />
Hunting in natimbi, I'm always running around with zero downtime usually.<br />
A fungal tunic and FT6 is enough to keep you charm killing almost non stop.<br />
I'll stop off in the bazaar to get some mage summoned weapons and haste mask, charm a mastruq in natimbi, equip him, and mow through about 15 hynids and turupa and stonemites before my pet is low enough health that it's worth it for me to kill him for more xp, and find a new pet to equip.<br />
I've also had some fun doing mass charm kiting in Dulak harbor, keeping about 5 or 6 mobs in camp at all times (aggro 5 mobs, charm one, send pet, the other 4 jump it, invis when pet low health, chant kite pet to death, find another add, charm, repeat...)<br />
It's fairly hectic, but rather fun.<br />
If you can type with any decent amount of speed, you can type some stuff out while still twisting.<br />
You basicly have 3 seconds to type something before the next song needs to be twisted in.<br />
If you are content with just twisting 3 songs, you get about 5 seconds to type stuff.<br />
So some of what you say is fragmented, but the group understands.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
One of the best parts is bards don't take that much cash to twink up at the basic level.<br />
If you want to get into heavy charming of mobs, that's where the cash flow increases a lot (~100k for FT3 boots or ornate boots, ~50k for mask of contemplation, ~5k for earring of solstace), and having a fungi is always useful.<br />
Bards don't tank primarily though, so you can get by with substandard armor.<br />
Just make sure you have a decent haste item, and get some armor/weapons with instrument mods if you can.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/mpatterson64/juujuusigsmall.jpg" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=364111" target="_blank">Juujuu Bigmojo</a> <br />
70 Human Shaman<br />
