</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>ROFL, as a bard mod, I have to agree with many of you here that by far, a bard is the most intensive class to play well, and as for typing, a good TYPIST can get out 3 or so short words per song cast.  As for getting 4 songs going, it had little to nothing to do with manual dexterity or the skill of the player, but rather your computer and internet connection, plus any crowd lag.  A good bard can keep however many songs up their system/lag can handle, all the time. A great bard can keep up that many songs that are the best for that particular situation, changing the twist to fit the precise need of the group.  An insane bard pulls, melees, hastes, slows, DS's, snares and performs crowd control, all at the same time... Believe me, one LDoN of that and you log your cleric for an hour or two. hehe.  Oh yeah, and I've played every class but a chanter, but would have to say that a bard doing CC is much harder than a chanter, for many reasons.  As for playing a class well, I'd say necro's second hardest, but that's just personal opinion.<br />
<br />
Let me end with saying I love my shaman, he's awesome, fun to solo, not so fun to play MHealer, but great to play when I have only an hour or less to kill.  Thanks for the great forum!<br />
<br />
Seremont</p>
	
	
	
	
	
