	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I agree with bards, but you do have to be able to cope with the mechanism. Practice twisting three songs for a while and then imagine trying to do that for a couple of hours. Not for me, I know that.<br />
<br />
Enchanter is probably next. But they tend to alternate between extreme boredom and hectic activity. Being a chanter in a pickup grind group just looks dull beyond words.<br />
<br />
Tanks and clerics are actually not bad choices, though people joke about it. A good tank or cleric is always doing something in a group, always watching the environment and ready to respond. The problem with a cleric is that it's a very passive role which can become dispiriting. Not quite as passive as the primary healer shaman though, yawn (I only made it to 55). You can't solo, but at least you get to keep the use of your wrists.<br />
<br />
Basically if you play something which has a strong role then that will be reflected in stuff for you to do.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
