<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Juujuu</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 1999<br />
	Location: Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Practice twisting three songs for a while and then imagine trying to do that for a couple of hours. Not for me, I know that.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Ya.   We should do something much less tedious like, say, cannidancing...   <img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="roll eyes (sarcastic)" smilieid="8" /> <br />
<br />
I tried making a bard about a year ago.<br />
I didn't have my hotkeys in any particularly good setup, and so I hated the bard and deleted it after about 3 levels.<br />
I wanted to try it again a while later, and set up my hotkeys in a much different way, and now I've got a 57 bard that's quite fun to play.<br />
<br />
I've set up my 1-7 and 0 keypad numbers to cast spells 1-7 and 8 respectively.<br />
I have my fdse keys set up to control my movement as I do in all first person shooters.<br />
I've also got some really major wrist support happening because my wrists were hurting a lot from just playing a shaman, nevermind starting to play a bard.<br />
(I've got a towel rolled up and flattened out lying down in front of my keyboard that I rest my wrists on when I play so my wrists are completely straight when I'm at the keyboard and don't need to strain any muscles to be able to type or hit keys.)<br />
<br />
Once you have a decent hotkey setup, twisting songs isn't hard.<br />
It's pretty much just learning to count in pairs.<br />
My main songs I twist in combat when I'm not mezzing or charming or whatever is haste, overhaste, mana regen, and slow/snare which are songs 1 2 3 4 for me.<br />
When I'm meleeing stuff, I'm hitting keys 1 1 2 2 3 3 4 4 1 1 2 2 3 3 4 4 ... in succession whenever my song has finished casting.<br />
If I need to do something else, like mez an add, while still meleeing I'll probably change the pattern to 1 1 2 2 3 3 ~ 6 ~ 6 1 1 2 2 3 3 ~ 6 ~ ... in which 6 is my mez and ~ is my hotkey to change between last 2 targets.<br />
It's not really that difficult once you've tried it a bit.</p>
	
	
	
