	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Most high end bards I know use game pads for twisting.<br />
<br />
As some have pointed out, how hard a class is can be situational.<br />
<br />
Soloing, Warriors, Rogues, Clerics have it hard.<br />
<br />
In a balanced group, I think all classes are about even.<br />
<br />
In Raid some classes are definately harder than others. Both Clerics and Chanters require a high degree of concentration when their skills are needed. AKA cheal chains and CC jails.<br />
<br />
I think the question should be what style of play do you find most fun. Some people love playing warriors others hate it. Same with Clerics, etc.</p>
	
	
	
