	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Zillanex</b><br /><i>Bards are fun and the ability to quad kite without downtime is sweet...]</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Bards don't quad kite really, they Ae kite, which means as many mobs as your video card/pc can handle without lag you too much.<br />
To do that it really require manual dexterity and timing or you will die way too often. Soloing with my Bard is been so far the most amazing experience I had with EQ, you can handle high reds/trains in a way that you would never do with any other class. High mobility and ability to track or outrun every mob let you scout about every outdoor zone. On the negative side, you will get burned out very fast because after a while,  playing will not be very relaxing having to twist songs constantly and if you group , to do something different, to be bossed around by people that don't know what they are doing or having to wait forever before they start pulling.<br />
Play an enchanter is not easy because of the frustration of dieing when people constantly break mezzes.<br />
<br />
-Stanislao</p>
	
	
	
	
	
